    "collapsible_content_html_zJhpAX": {
      "type": "collapsible-content-html",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_UXcXWV": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Polymorphic light eruption (PMLE)",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>In placebo-controlled studies of around 80 PMLE patients, daily oral Fernblock® during sun exposure significantly reduced skin reactions and symptoms; 74% of those continuing use through summer reported minimal or no recurrence.<sup>7,8</sup></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_wMftQy": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Vitiligo",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Placebo-controlled studies show improved re-pigmentation and higher response rates when oral Fernblock® is combined with NB-UVB phototherapy versus phototherapy alone, with effects also linked to reduced CD3/CD25 T-cell activity in PUVA regimens.<sup>9</sup></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_8TUaE6": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Melasma & hyperpigmentation",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Oral Fernblock® as an adjunct to hydroquinone and sunscreen produced significantly greater and faster mMASI score improvements than placebo, with 31% of patients achieving ≥75% improvement versus 6% on placebo alone.<sup>10</sup></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_Gpz9kQ": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Photoageing & environmental oxidative stress",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Studies show Fernblock® reduces UV- and pollution-induced ROS, MMP-1 collagen breakdown, and mitochondrial damage, while protecting Langerhans cells and fibroblasts against visible light and infrared-A exposure in vitro and in vivo.<sup>11</sup></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_9nJGCn": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Actinic keratosis (AK)",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Studies show oral and topical Fernblock® as an adjunct to PDT and cryotherapy improves AK clearance and AKASI scores versus standard care alone, with reviews reporting reduced CPDs, p53 activation, and lower recurrence risk.<sup>12</sup></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
